body:
@nicoddemus the documentation uses `pytest_cmdline_preparse` in one example:

https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/example/simple.html#dynamically-adding-command-line-options

Should it be updated to use `pytest_load_initial_conftests` ?

@jxramos thanks.

It was deprecated in [`7.0.0rc1`](https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/blob/main/doc/en/changelog.rst#pytest-700rc1-2021-12-06), but we did not add the respective changelog entry about its removal in `8.1.0`.

Would you like to contribute a PR amending the changelog?
